image_desc: Photo by Joyce Lye 赖玉珠 on December 10, 2020. May be an image of 2 people, hair and people standing.
text:
“How nice if I can join the Sangha group of Tzu Chi in Hualian, Taiwan.” That was my thought when my hair was shaved in 2015. Even though, my intention then was to raise $50,000 for the Compassion Support Scheme for cancer patients of all age groups. 

This year , I have just completed my 3-km daily walk from home to my office at Aljunied Crescent for 151 days during 2020 Cut Cut Cut - Cut For Compassion event. For every km I'd walked, I raised $10 for Kampung Senang. I was very reluctant to walk since becoming a mum 30 years ago, and would rely on driving even for a distance of just 2 km. A friend of donkey years challenged me by pledging a donation of $ 10 per km to Kampung Senang if I could walk to work and reduce carbon emission.

This year, besides walking a distance of 453 km , I have set the event target higher at $80,000 due to increased needs of people affected by both mental health issues and chronic illnesses. So far, we've raised only $41,000. If we can find donors for an additional $40,000, I have promised to shave my hair again. 

I sincerely hope to keep that promise.
https://www.kampungsenang.org/compassion-fund/

#socialservicesgconnect

With Covid-19 on a rampage, many of us are at the end of our tethers, ready to fly off our handles. Frustration is nationwide at best, and suffocation is an understatement for many of us deprived of roaming our frequent haunts with the people we love. 😩😩😩⁣
⁣
Altogether, the year has been an overwhelmingly dark one for billions of people all over the world. While that is the reality, this is also a reality : 𝘞𝘦 𝘨𝘦𝘵 𝘵𝘰 𝘤𝘩𝘰𝘰𝘴𝘦 𝘵𝘰 𝘚𝘦𝘦 𝘛𝘩𝘦 𝘓𝘪𝘨𝘩𝘵. 🌟🌟🌟⁣
⁣
Despite the terrible hand that we have been dealt with, we get to choose to play our cards the best way we can. Despite the storm of death and destruction that the virus has brought, we get to choose to see the very best of humanity - our frontline heroes - resilient and resolved in this fight. 𝘋𝘦𝘴𝘱𝘪𝘵𝘦 𝘵𝘩𝘦 𝘥𝘢𝘳𝘬𝘯𝘦𝘴𝘴, we get to choose to see the good in whatever situation we are in.⁣
⁣
We get to choose to 𝘚𝘦𝘦 𝘛𝘩𝘦 𝘓𝘪𝘨𝘩𝘵.⁣
⁣
“𝐃𝐞𝐬𝐩𝐢𝐭𝐞 𝐂𝐨𝐯𝐢𝐝-𝟏𝟗, 𝐈 𝐚𝐦 𝐇𝐎𝐏𝐄𝐅𝐔𝐋”

image_desc: Photo by 🌹Yvaine • 欣🎀 on December 29, 2020. May be an image of 3 people and hair.
text:
#throwbackto #may2020 #circuitbreakersg 

CB was a period where each individual evolved into someone they wasn't due to desperate needs yet unavailable resources.

"Holidays" would be ending soon; the boys hair were growing like hay. Our usual hairdresser, aka 婆婆, wasn't able to pop by our place to help trim their hair (or vice versa), due to CB restrictions. 

So i transformed myself into that home-based amateur hairdresser; borrowed my mum's hairdressing tools and got the job done myself.

Not as fantastic looking. Oh wells... I tried. At least no longer long and still looked reasonable for school.

#劉家男孩 #我家两宝

text:
年末のシンガポールは風が強い、雨が降った後は気温が一気に23-24度に下がり、かなり寒いです😨 こんな日は暖かい料理が食べたい気分❣️

今日の夕食はインドネシア風の甘酸味調味料Masak Merahをチキン、トマト、茄子とじゃがいも入りの煮物にしました〜スープは多目にして、残りのRussian Bread と一緒に食べました〜😋 寒い日はやはり身体がポカポカになる料理だね❣️

YouTubeで生食パンをホームベーカリーで作るレシピを見て〜丁度生クリームが有り、試しに作りました😆 

ホームベーカリーで生地を捏ね+２次発酵、生地を出し食パン型に入れ、2/3分の高さまで発酵したら、オーブンに入れ180度15分>160度15分で焼き上がり❣️

綺麗な食パンが初めて焼けて〜🍞…めちゃ嬉しい😆 
しかも食感がふわふわでモッチリ〜美味しい❣️
生クリーム入りでこんな食パン🍞が出来るとは…
素晴らしいです❣️これから我が家の定番にしよう👌

皆さん良い日を❣️Stay Safe & Healthy 

年末的季候風 風特別大
由其雨后 气溫下降 冷風颼颼 
这时候吃热乎乎的食物 最棒了！
晚餐煮了一鍋用印尼式的Masak Merah 调味酱
燜煮半只鸡、番茄、马铃薯和茄子 再搭配剩余的罗宋面包 
簡單又美味 身心也暖起來了～❤️

前阵子从Youtube见到日式吐司 🍞 的recipe 
面团要加入Whipped cream 
刚好冰箱还剩不少whipped cream 就取之試試
用bread maker进行Kneading 和二次發酵
取出放进吐司模型 再继续犮酵至兩倍
接著进烤箱烘焙 没想到居然初次可以烤到这么美 👍
让我惊讶 也太棒了👏
原來加whipped cream後的吐司 口感是这么软松 
口感好像在日本吃到的吐司🍞那样❗️
賛！決定列入家常面包名單中❣️

㊗️大家 幸福平安 Happy Holidays

"Titus, I did not push her, she moved to make some room for me. It is a large chair. Just because your bum won't fit on the chair doesn't mean that mine won't either."

"Vanilla, you're rude. You need to learn some manners."

image_desc: Photo by 🌹Yvaine • 欣🎀 on December 29, 2020. May be a closeup of 1 person and hair.
text:
#throwbackto #may2020 #欣2020爱你爱妳 #circuitbreakersg 

Pictured here with make up and in work formal attire; this was the new norm; getting dressed up at home and having interviews/meetings via zoom. This was like the don't know how many interviews i had, after sending in hundreds of job applications. End of interviews responses were almost similar; "We do not know when we can be back in office, we will still be in touch with you again.".

***

One of my resolutions for 2020 was to get back to workforce after my long hiatus of being out of the working society.

When i first made the decision to be a homemaker 7 years back, i wasn't expecting myself to be "out" for so long.

All these years, i did try to "get out" of my own current circumstances. It wasn't easy as kids' well-being and matters are always on mind; not easy to let go of a lot when I've been so hands-on with them.

In 2016, i finally stepped out and did some job searching. Was delighted that i managed to get a job offered not long after. However, we had an accidental blessing when I found out i was pregnant with #babygirl, before i signed the offer contract. Employer wasn't accepting towards my pregnancy; pretty much expected; my job offer was withdrawn.

Oh wells... Here comes another year(s) of homemaking life.

After giving birth in 2017, i decided that i should complete my degree prior to going back to workforce; at least i could have a nice portfolio as i upgraded myself during my hiatus off working society.

Another year and two passed; i finished my last paper in Dec 2018 while full-time caring for the youngest at home. Woohoo! So much effort and commitment. I finally made it.

2019 came along and i thot "yeah yeah!"; No obstruction for me to get a job. Was so looking forward.

As #bigboy advanced into his next stage of life, i thot i can settle him a little first before i start and focus more on job searching. Who knew just into the first Saturday of 2019, i had that freaky accident at home that left me handicapped for a few months. WHAT! Then physical destruction from head to toes came subsequently; caused by the effect of medications, x-rays etc etc.

(Continued in Comment)

image_desc: Photo by Muiee メイ on December 28, 2020.
text:
昨晩焼いたRussian Bread を朝食に❣️シンガポールのベーカリーにあんまりかほぼ見かけないRussian Bread, マレーシア、台湾や香港のベーカリーには良く買えるんですが、何故かシンガポールでは見えない😂 中国語では”羅宋麵包” と呼んで、その羅宋は上海語発音のRussian から❗️なるほど〜ロシアの赤いボロシチスープも”羅宋湯”と呼んでいて……やっと謎が解けた❗️😆

作り方はそんなに難しく無いが、色んなレシピが有り、今回はシンプルバージョンから試しました〜食感がふわふわで上のバター🧈が香ばしい〜旦那氏も👍 次はサクサク感をしたRussian Breadを作りたいです❣️

昨晩の夕食はSpinach Mushroom Pizza 
キャストアイロンのフライパンで焼くピザは生地がサクサクして美味しい❣️

皆さん良い日を❣️2020年もそろそろ終わり〜Stay Safe & Healthy 💪

昨晚烤好的罗宋面包 🥖

说到罗宋面包 我和老爷都喜歡 然而在這里的Bakery
很难买到 以前越提去JB 很常在Lavendar Bakery买回來 
昨天想到这面包 查看做法後 就試試 
Shaping 还需要多进步 😂 手残 型做的不好
不過味道有像  這recipe 罗宋面包口感是软的 
还不錯  下次试用汤种的方法 

PS: 原来罗宋是上海发音的俄罗斯🇷🇺 😂 又長知识了
难怪以前在马来西亚买这个面包时 奇怪怎么叫罗宋 
那个俄罗斯有名的红红Borcsht 汤 也叫罗宋汤  一直不解
原来是发音的称呼呀！我那多年的谜题 终于解开了～ 😂

㊗️大家 幸福平安 Happy Holidays

image_desc: Photo by 【仪日行】michelle chia on December 28, 2020. May be a closeup of 1 person and flower.
text:
When the fringe looks like drawn curtains in the mornings 🙄 
你们喝水了吗？ 

#throwback #circuitbreakersg #cutmyownbangs

When the entire world goes into a holiday frenzy, it feels as if we cannot be anything but happy. 🥲⁣
⁣
We are bombarded with ads of smiling families feasting on Christmas goodies, our social media feeds are filled to the brim with festive greetings, and holiday music seems to blare from every available loudspeaker. ⁣
⁣
Everyone seems so 𝘨𝘳𝘢𝘵𝘦𝘧𝘶𝘭 and 𝘵𝘩𝘢𝘯𝘬𝘧𝘶𝘭, and it feels almost sinful not to partake in the celebrations wholeheartedly. ⁣
⁣
But, we know that isn’t the reality. ⁣
⁣
For some of us, the holidays are a great source of pain - a sobering reminder of 𝐛𝐫𝐨𝐤𝐞𝐧 𝐝𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐦𝐬, 𝐫𝐞𝐥𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧𝐬𝐡𝐢𝐩𝐬, 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐟𝐚𝐦𝐢𝐥𝐢𝐞𝐬. To others, it is the absence of what once was. Sometimes, the grandness of the  hustle and bustle makes us feel small and insignificant; a lonely blink amidst a vast backdrop.👤 ⁣
⁣
2020 has been 𝘲𝘶𝘪𝘵𝘦 𝘵𝘩𝘦 𝘺𝘦𝘢𝘳 hasn’t it? ⁣
⁣
As the year comes to a close, this is a reminder that we are not alone. No matter how dark the year has been, there are people who know too well the struggles you go through.⁣
 ⁣
You are 𝘯𝘰𝘵 𝘢𝘭𝘰𝘯𝘦. ❤⁣
⁣

Each artwork consists of long exposure of exactly one hour, and a multi-exposure of 60 photographs taken every 60 seconds over the same hour.'.
text:
Happy publication day to @wwyart’s Pandemic Time!
A collaborative project that brings together 24 poets working in Singapore to write through each hour of the day in response to time, which has become innumerable in this ridiculous year. As the first poem I’ve had published in Singapore, it’s a delight and a privilege to be included here alongside friends.

The poems and recordings are available at https://pandemictime.org.

text:
.
先輩に手作りのシュトーレンとクッキーを贈りに都会へ行きました〜

優しい先輩から又プレゼントを貰い、本当に有り難うございました💕  SunnyHillsの新品”柚香蘋果酥” (Yuzu Apple Cake) ❣️柚子の皮と青森红玉りんごの果肉をたっぷり入れた、爽やかと甘い味のハーモニー、とても美味しかったです👍 

皆さん良い日を❣️Stay Safe & Healthy 👍

予约看脚踏车🚲 也顺道把圣诞goodies~ 
Stollen和cookies交给住在市区的前辈❣️
也再次谢谢 她送的Sunny Hills 微热山丘 
新口味的柚香苹果酥 好好吃哦😋～ 
可以咬到香气浓郁的柚子皮
还有香甜的苹果肉 (使用了青森红玉苹果）老爷大愛❣️ 
一直瞄着盒子 问可以再吃多一点吗……😆
(叫他饭后再吃 想必明天就被吃完了）

Yuzu-Apple Cake  超推👍
微热山丘 @sunnyhillssg 的包装 很适合送礼或自用
刚看了网站 已经推出了农历新年版本的礼盒🎁
有兴趣的朋友 可以查询官网 http://sunnyhills.com.sg

㊗️大家 Happy Holidays & Merry Christmas 🎄❄️☃️

image_desc: Photo shared by Cheng Wei May Lee on December 25, 2020 tagging @pix_story. May be an image of 2 people, hair, biceps, people standing and text that says 'BRING THE SHOW'.
text:
Every Friday, I go for #torturewithleonard , and if I am lucky enough to book a #bodybalance slot, #fridaywithsean (though often he manages to make it #torturewithsean with some crazy Pilates) Two completely different workouts, but I always feel so good and ready for the weekend after. Glad I was able to do both on this Christmas Day and last Friday of 2020!

This year, I totally changed my mindset towards keeping fit and have found more enjoyment and fulfilllment from my time in the gym / working out more than ever. For the first time in my life (and especially after lockdown during #circuitbreakersg), I try to give attention to various aspects of fitness- cardio, strength, core, balance, flexibility etcetc (albeit not at all equal).

Sometimes, I feel bad that I can no longer run 10km daily & 21km whenever I feel like it, but in some ways, I have gained much more!

Everyone says I’m lucky to be so “fit” because I could run everyday (slowly)- disciplined and stubborn maybe, but definitely not fit! When I was 30, I couldn’t even do five burpees, hold a plank or jump up a bench! 

Everyone starts somewhere, and fitness is just a continuous journey you do for your mind and body, and most importantly, for yourself. 

In the coming year(s), I want to add my “finger fitness” back to my regime- started the Christmas morning listening to Debussy and then practicing the piano arrangement of Grieg’s Holberg Suite on, and it was wonderful.

image_desc: Photo by INONE Story in Singapore. May be an image of text that says 'BEAUTY IN THE BROKEN'.
text:
⁣
𝘒𝘪𝘯𝘵𝘴𝘶𝘨𝘪, also known as Kintsukuroi,  is the Japanese art of restoring broken pottery with lacquered resin and powdered gold.⁣
⁣
The beauty of Kintsugi lies in its unapologetic display of each and every imperfection. They are displayed proudly in gold, and not hidden away. Each piece passes through masterful hands in the restoration process, and every fracture and flaw is honoured as a testament to its rich history.⁣
⁣
The resulting masterpieces are uniquely beautiful, and risen in value.⁣
⁣
Brokenness - that is one thing we all have in common. We all live with some form of brokenness - broken hearts, shattered dreams, crushed hopes, failing friendships or splintered families. ⁣
⁣
We shy away from our flaws and imperfections, desperately keeping them away from the light of day. We keep them hidden and stored away in the lockers of our hearts. We regard them as weaknesses that could be exploited if we happen to let the walls, that we have put up to keep us safe, down.⁣
⁣
Perhaps the scars we all bear are the greatest sources of our strength. Perhaps our imperfections are indicators that we are not programmed robots. Perhaps our brokenness is but a reminder - that we are living and breathing despite the pain.⁣
Perhaps everything beautiful, brilliant, and gorgeous about us  is not only found in what we are comfortable with showing, but also in the imperfections and scars we choose to hide.⁣
⁣
There is 𝐛𝐞𝐚𝐮𝐭𝐲 𝐢𝐧 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐛𝐫𝐨𝐤𝐞𝐧.⁣

image_desc: Photo shared by ONEおね Patisserie on December 23, 2020 tagging @one.o.nepatisserie.
text:
𝓒𝓱𝓻𝓲𝓼𝓽𝓶𝓪𝓼 🎄𝓔𝓿𝓮. Are you organized & ready for gatherings? ⛄️

It’s been an interesting 2020, many are able to celebrate this end of year on a positive note as we welcome Phase 3 😌

It’s been a heartening period running this home business as we handmake each cake and helped many gift their loved ones with sweet messages. Here’s reviewing this unique year with some pictures. Have you gotten any of these? 

We started this biz in April 2020 as the world flustered & Singapore going into 𝘊𝘪𝘳𝘤𝘶𝘪𝘵 𝘉𝘳𝘦𝘢𝘬𝘦𝘳 with several rules and restrictions for home biz. 

In May, we had small dessert boxes gifted with many many “𝘚𝘵𝘢𝘺 𝘚𝘢𝘧𝘦” messages to encourage their family and friends amidst the uncertainty during 𝘊𝘪𝘳𝘤𝘶𝘪𝘵 𝘉𝘳𝘦𝘢𝘬𝘦𝘳. (𝘗𝘪𝘤 2)

When 𝘗𝘩𝘢𝘴𝘦 1 arrived in June, Dessert Boxes & ChiffONE Boxes were gifted by corporate & friends with “𝘑𝘪𝘢𝘺𝘰𝘶” messages. Many are still WFH...cabin fever and mental health awareness increases as we had been staying at home! (𝘗𝘪𝘤 3 & 4)

We were very thankful to be featured on 𝑻𝒉𝒆 𝑺𝒕𝒓𝒂𝒊𝒕𝒔 𝑻𝒊𝒎𝒆𝒔 for our limited edition 𝑵𝒂𝒕𝒊𝒐𝒏𝒂𝒍 𝑫𝒂𝒚 Specials!  It was tediously great fun to create our 🇸🇬 flag with 🍓 ! (𝘗𝘪𝘤 5) 

Since Sep, as more return to offices (yay or nay 🤣), 𝘾𝙝𝙞𝙛𝙛𝙊𝙉𝙀 𝘽𝙤𝙭𝙚𝙨 continue to be very popular as many love to try all flavors! We individually wrap each slice for easy pantry-food in office! (𝘗𝘪𝘤 4). 

There are many Sep, Oct & Nov babies... or is it that small gatherings are finally allowed? Rose Chiffon cakes is loved for being a light cake but our Strawberry Fresh Cream Cake is the most popular for birthdays!  And what if our customer love both our rose & strawberry cake...we had a customized 𝑺𝒕𝒓𝒂𝒘𝒃𝒆𝒓𝒓𝒚 & 𝑹𝒐𝒔𝒆 𝑭𝒓𝒆𝒔𝒉 𝑪𝒓𝒆𝒂𝒎 𝑪𝒂𝒌𝒆! (𝘗𝘪𝘤 6). Will you like to try it too? 

Mulled Wine is “the 🎄 drink” for me and family, and what’s better than creating 𝑴𝒖𝒍𝒍𝒆𝒅 𝑾𝒊𝒏𝒆 𝑳𝒐𝒈 𝑪𝒂𝒌𝒆? (𝘗𝘪𝘤 7)

Our Christmas Special has to have our signature too, 𝑺𝒕𝒓𝒂𝒘𝒃𝒆𝒓𝒓𝒚 𝑭𝒓𝒆𝒔𝒉 𝑪𝒓𝒆𝒂𝒎 𝑳𝒐𝒈 𝑪𝒂𝒌𝒆! (𝘗𝘪𝘤 8)

Thankful for all the support. 

𝓜𝓮𝓻𝓻𝔂 𝓒𝓱𝓻𝓲𝓼𝓽𝓶𝓪𝓼 !

image_desc: Photo by GRUB Burger Bistro (Bishan) on December 23, 2020. May be an image of one or more people, french fries and burger.
text:
Blessed Christmas Grubbers! 🎄Thank you for being with us through this crazy year unlike any other. It was an honour to visit your homes during #circuitbreakersg, and to feed you in the park, some of you coming from the far corners of #Singapore to visit us in #Bishan. 

We are looking forward to serving you on Christmas Day. Last few slots for 9am and 10.30am are still available so head over to www.grub.com.sg/reservation, and we will see you tomorrow! 🎉
